div.h1: Kernel Heap: kmalloc Virtual Address Space Layout
div.p: Virtual Range: 0xD0000000 - 0xDFFFFFFF (256MB heap space)

g.text: kmalloc SPLIT Operation: Before and After
kfree COALESCE Operation: Before and After
heap_expand: Map New Physical Frame When Heap Exhausted

div.p: Green = allocated block
Blue = free block
Purple = block header metadata
Red = fragmentation danger
Orange = heap expansion

g.text: Page 1+ [0xD0001000-0xDFFFFFFF] NOT MAPPED: access triggers page fault 14
offset 4-7: size uint32_t (usable bytes, excludes header)
offset 12-15: next ptr forward link (NULL = end of heap)
offset 16-19: prev ptr backward link (enables O(1) coalescing)
BEFORE: one free block [148 bytes usable]
AFTER kfree(ptr_B): one large free block
Trigger: last block cannot satisfy kmalloc(N)
Extend or create free block covering new page
Retry kmalloc scan: new block satisfies request
Internal Fragmentation: waste INSIDE a block
Block D: FREE [3636 bytes remainder of page 0]

div.p: kmalloc(4) uses 24 bytes -> 500% overhead
kmalloc(64) uses 84 bytes -> 31% overhead
kmalloc(4096) uses 4116 bytes -> 0.5% overhead
Fix: size-class slabs eliminate per-obj headers

g.text: Block A: FREE [96 bytes] prev=BlockC next=BlockB
Block B: ALLOCATED [64 bytes] ptr_B points here
Block C: FREE [200 bytes] prev=BlockB next=NULL
Step 1: Validate header magic and free flag
Step 3: Coalesce NEXT if Block C is free
Step 4: Coalesce PREV if Block A is free
Step 5: Update search_hint to freed addr if earlier
Block A+B+C MERGED: FREE [400 bytes usable]

div.p: If last block free: last->size += PAGE_SIZE
Else: new block at heap_end - PAGE_SIZE
size = PAGE_SIZE - sizeof(header)
Cause: size rounded to 8-byte alignment boundary
kmalloc(33) rounds to 40, wastes 7 bytes per block
Mitigation: size = (size+7) and NOT 7 alignment
Production fix: size-class slabs (zero internal frag per class)
Cause: alternating alloc/free leaves non-contiguous holes
Metric: largest_contiguous_free / total_free
Mitigation: immediate coalescing in kfree via prev ptr O(1)
Production fix: buddy allocator (zero ext frag, more int frag)
First-fit: O(n) search, Medium ext-frag, Low int-frag, Good cache
Next-fit: O(1) avg, Medium ext-frag, Low int-frag, Best cache
Best-fit: O(n) search, Low ext-frag, Medium int-frag, Poor cache
Buddy: O(log n), None ext-frag, High int-frag, OK cache
Slab/SLUB: O(1), None ext-frag, None int-frag, Best cache
This kernel uses next-fit via search_hint pointer.
Linux SLUB used for fixed-size kernel objects.
kmalloc(33) rounds up to 40, wastes 7 bytes
Internal frag = allocated_size - requested_size
Mitigated by 8-byte alignment rounding in kmalloc
96 + 200 = 296 bytes free BUT split across 2 blocks
kmalloc(250) FAILS even though total free >= 250
External fragmentation: contiguous space unavailable
block->size += sizeof(header) + next->size
block->next = block->next->next (NULL)
prev->size += sizeof(header) + block->size
prev->next = block->next (NULL)

g.text: Header: size=400 free=1 (Block A is merged root)
400 bytes contiguous free: kmalloc(250) now SUCCEEDS
next ptr: Block A -> Block B (forward link)
prev ptr: Block B -> Block A (O(1) coalesce)
heap_expand called when b3 cannot satisfy request
last block too small -> triggers heap_expand
header layout drives split threshold (20+8=28 min remainder)
prev+next pointers enable O(1) bidirectional coalesce
